1
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,200
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

2
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:22,760
(GUNFIRE)

3
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,800
(GRUNTS)

4
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,000
What's wrong?

5
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:53,400
Was that a child?

6
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,680
(PANTING)

7
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:01,600
KANZO: Oi!

8
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,680
You, there! Stop!

9
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,800
Stop running!

10
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,280
It's OK.

11
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:10,000
Not going to hurt you.

12
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:12,240
Just don't run.

13
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:14,080
-Kanzo?
-I'll catch up!

14
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,760
There are clam drones two miles away.

15
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,840
KANZO: I know. I'll be fine.

16
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,560
Just go.

17
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:24,360
What are you doing out here?

18
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:27,400
Huh? Did you get lost?

19
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:35,840
Stay still! Stay absolutely still.

20
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:41,160
(BEEPING)

21
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,840
I'm just scanning the ground.

22
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:45,000
I think we've got company.

23
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,800
Do you know what hand mines are?

24
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,760
(GASPS)

25
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:55,960
Well, in that case, you know you've got
to stand absolutely still, right?

26
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:01,720
Ever seen a hand mine?

27
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,360
Where?

28
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,880
(PANTING)

29
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:07,960
(GASPS)

30
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,920
OK.

31
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,240
It's OK.

32
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,280
Everything's going to be f...

33
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,960
(PANTING)

34
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,240
Help me!

35
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,040
Someone, please!

36
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,280
Help me!

37
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,680
Help me!

38
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,760
(ELECTRONIC PULSE)

39
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:16,440
DOCTOR: Your chances of survival
are about one in a thousand,

40
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,040
so here's what you do.

41
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,440
You forget the thousand and
you concentrate on the one.

42
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:22,320
Pick it up!

43
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:27,040
I said, pick it up!

44
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,120
(ELECTRONIC PULSE)

45
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:38,120
DOCTOR: I'm straight ahead of you,
about 50 feet. Can you see me?

46
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:45,040
The device in your hand is
creating an acoustic corridor,

47
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,080
so that we can talk. Do you understand?

48
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:49,480
Who are you?

49
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,280
DOCTOR: Oh, I'm just a passer-by.

50
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:54,000
I was looking for a bookshop.
How do you think I'm doing?

51
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:56,480
BOY: This isn't a bookshop.
DOCTOR: No, this is a war.

52
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,240
A very old one,
going by the mix of technology.

53
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:02,080
Which war is this?
I get them all muddled up.

54
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,600
Just "the war."”

55
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,240
Where am I? What planet is this?

56
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,640
I don't understand.

57
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,800
DOCTOR: Oh, well, neither do I.

58
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:12,400
I try never to understand.
It's called "an open mind."

59
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:15,760
Now you have got to make a choice.

60
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
A choice?

61
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:19,960
Yes, you have got to decide
that you're going to live.

62
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,480
Survival is just a choice.
Choose it now.

63
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,200
If I move, they'll get me.

64
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:30,640
I told you, you have
one chance in a thousand,

65
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,960
but one is all you ever need.

66
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,120
What's your name?

67
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,320
Come on. Faith in the future!

68
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,600
Introduce yourself!

69
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:48,000
Tell me the name of the boy
who isn't going to die today.

70
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,800
Davros.

71
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,080
My name is Davros.

72
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,800
DAVROS: Hello?

73
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,760
Are you still there?

74
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:05,000
Please, you've got to help me.

75
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,040
You said I could survive,
you said you'd help me!

76
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:11,760
Help me!

77
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,800
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

78
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,160
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

79
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,880
(CHATTER DIES DOWN)

80
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,360
(GROWLING)

81
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,880
We are Colony Sarff.

82
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,880
We bring harm.

83
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:38,880
Where is the Doctor?

84
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,520
(GROWLING)

85
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:52,320
Where is the Doctor?

86
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:59,520
(HISSING)

87
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,440
(GRUNTING)

88
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:09,280
(SHOUTS) Where is the Doctor?

89
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:18,320
SHADOW ARCHITECT: Deploy the
under-regiment, across both sectors.

90
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,720
That number of suicide moons
cannot be ignored.

91
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:25,640
Apparently, we have a security breach.

92
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,240
I won't ask how you got in here.

93
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:32,240
But I will demand to know your business,

94
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,480
Colony Sarff.

95
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,320
Where is the Doctor?

96
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:43,280
I've no idea.

97
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,680
He's not our concern,

98
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:49,000
and he's certainly not your employer's.

99
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:52,800
The Doctor is required.

100
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,040
SHADOW ARCHITECT: For what?

101
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,920
Colony Sarff,

102
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,400
you need to tell me

103
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:02,680
what does Davros want with the Doctor?

104
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,400
(HISSES)

105
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,520
(THUNDER)

106
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,120
OHILA: (ECHOING) Welcome, Colony Sarff.

107
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,880
We are the Sisterhood of Karn.

108
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,520
If you do not leave
our world immediately,

109
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,360
we will take your skin.

110
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,120
Where is the Doctor?

111
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,560
OHILA: Where he always is.

112
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,480
Right behind you,

113
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,480
and one step ahead.

114
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:48,320
Tread carefully when you seek the
Doctor, Colony Sarff,

115
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,560
or he will be the last thing you find.

116
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:56,680
Davros, creator of the Daleks,
Dark Lord of Skaro...

117
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:57,760
What of him?

118
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,640
Davros is dying.

119
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,640
Davros is ancient.

120
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,320
He should have been dust centuries ago.

121
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,400
He has a message for the Doctor.

122
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,920
Then you will give it to me.

123
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,520
(HISSING)

124
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,920
(GRUNTING)

125
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,560
OHILA: Your powers mean nothing here.

126
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,000
Give me the message and leave.

127
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:22,320
Tell the Doctor...

128
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,800
Davros knows.

129
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,760
Davros remembers.

130
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,200
Tell him

131
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:35,600
he must face Davros one last time.

132
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,520
(THUNDER)

133
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,560
Davros knows.

134
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:47,200
Davros remembers.

135
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,160
(THUNDER)

136
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,680
Doctor?

137
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,520
What have you done?

138
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,480
DAVROS: Doctor.

139
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,920
Doctor.

140
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,520
(BEEPING)

141
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,840
(FEEBLY) Doctor.

142
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,320
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

143
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:23,160
COLONY SARFF:
You are dreaming, Lord Davros.

144
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,240
DAVROS: No.

145
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:29,760
I am anticipating.

146
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:33,000
He cannot be found.

147
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,080
DAVROS: Of course he can.

148
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:38,520
He has a weakness.

149
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,680
If you seek the Doctor,

150
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,760
first seek his friends.

151
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,080
RYAN: Will I get it back after school?

152
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,640
STUDENTS: Ew!

153
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,800
How will you know which one's yours?

154
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,160
(STUDENTS LAUGHING)

155
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,360
Fine then.

156
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:03,720
Right, now where was I?

157
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,280
Jane Austen.

158
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:08,080
Amazing writer,
brilliant comic observer,

159
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,120
and strictly amongst ourselves,
a phenomenal kisser.

160
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,400
Miss?

161
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,480
ALISON: Miss?

162
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,760
RYAN: Miss?

163
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:25,040
(STUDENTS CHATTERING)

164
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,800
Everybody, turn on their phones.

165
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,240
News websites and Twitter.

166
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,840
-Twitter?
-Hashtag...

167
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,200
...Planes Have Stopped.

168
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,600
REPORTER: Reports of planes

169
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,560
hanging apparently
motionless in the sky...

170
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,160
Footage of passenger jets,

171
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:55,120
which have seemingly
come to a complete stand-still...

172
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,080
Miss Oswald,
there's a call at the office.

173
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,640
-That would probably be UNIT.
-They say you're needed.

174
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,960
They were going to put me
through to the Prime Minister.

175
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,520
Mr Dunlop, sorry.

176
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:07,680
I have to take the rest of the day off
owing to a, um, personal crisis.

177
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:12,840
Yes! Yes, yes, yes, I'm coming!

178
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:16,480
No, don't send a helicopter.
Think it through.

179
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,000
AMERICAN REPORTER: Attempts
at communications

180
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,880
with pilots, crew, passengers,
all have failed.

181
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:27,880
Family members have held
candlelight vigils around the world.

182
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,360
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

183
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,800
REPORTER: Reports are coming in
from Caracas, Tel Aviv, Beijing.

184
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:36,440
It seems no corner
of the planet is unaffected.

185
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,720
The planes aren't responding.
No, none of them.

186
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,640
It's radio silence. I've got to go.

187
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,840
Tell the President I'll call him back.

188
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,160
He's not answering
his phone, have you tried?

189
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,320
We don't know enough yet.
He doesn't appreciate gossip.

190
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,400
Gossip?

191
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,840
How many planes?

192
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:57,000
4,165 aircraft currently airborne.

193
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,840
-That's a lot of passengers.
-That's a lot of fuel.

194
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:02,040
Oh, dear God. Yes, it is.

195
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,280
OK, so...

196
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,320
What could you do with
4,000 flying bombs?

197
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,880
Ah, well,

198
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:12,760
439 nuclear power stations
currently active.

199
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,160
What else?

200
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,360
I don't know, um, fault lines.

201
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,760
Earthquake. A tsunami?

202
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,560
Running simulations now.

203
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,440
So, if this is an attack...

204
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,520
What kind of attack advertises?

205
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,640
Why show somebody what you can do?
Why not just do it?

206
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,040
What's actually happened?
What are the pilots saying?

207
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,000
We can't contact them.

208
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,760
The planes haven't stopped,

209
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:37,080
they're actually frozen.
Like, frozen in time.

210
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,800
Pardon my sci-fi,

211
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:41,400
but this is beyond any human technology.

212
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,080
OK, so we need the Doctor.

213
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,560
Kate, we can't phone the Doctor
and bleat, he'll go Scottish.

214
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,960
Come on, what have we got,
what do we know?

215
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,440
It's not an attack,
it's not an invasion,

216
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:54,240
because, well, that doesn't
come with fair warning, so...

217
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:57,800
Somebody needs our attention.

218
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,840
Somebody who needs to put a gun to our
heads to make us listen. Oh!

219
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:01,920
KATE: Oh?

220
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,160
MIKE: We've got a message.
The Doctor channel.

221
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:06,640
Sorry, what?

222
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,960
He never uses it.

223
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:10,280
I doubt he remembers it even exists.

224
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,440
Then who is it?

225
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,240
MIKE: Decrypting...

226
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:17,560
-We're getting text through, I think.
-Texting? Definitely not the Doctor.

227
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,120
(BEEPING)

228
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:22,920
Have you got any more?

229
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,360
Coming.

230
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,040
Today, I shall be talking
to you out of...

231
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,480
-...the square window!
-What the hell was that?

232
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:43,560
How did she do that?

233
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:47,160
I dunno, some sort psychic
projection or something.

234
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,920
Oh, great, thanks.

235
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:52,560
OK, cutting to the chase, not dead.
Back. Big surprise, never mind.

236
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,640
I'm in a lovely little square
In one of your,

237
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,320
I don't know, hot countries,

238
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:58,240
and there's a light breeze
coming from the east,

239
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,360
and this coffee's
a buzz-monster in my brain

240
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,480
and I'm gonna need eight snipers.

241
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,800
Eight what?

242
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:05,640
MISSY: Three for each heart
and two for my brain stem.

243
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,760
You'll have to switch me off fast
before I can regenerate.

244
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,040
How fast can you get here?

245
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:11,360
Oh, I need to arrange
you a flight corridor.

246
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:12,920
Why do you need snipers?

247
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,800
Because it's the only way
she'll feel safe enough to talk to me.

248
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,120
Shall we say 4007?

249
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,760
(BELL TOLLING)

250
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,200
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

251
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,520
Oh!

252
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,640
(CHUCKLING)

253
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,080
Saucy.

254
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,520
(INAUDIBLE)

255
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,080
Go on then.

256
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,480
How's your boyfriend?

257
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:43,280
Still tremendously dead, I expect.

258
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:44,880
Still dead, yeah.

259
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,040
How come you're still alive?

260
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,160
Death is for other people, dear.

261
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:52,640
Would you like to sit in the shade?
I know how you humans burn.

262
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,720
(BEEPING)

263
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,720
(JET ENGINES ROARING)

264
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,200
Better?

265
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,840
I expect you've tried
to contact him by now.

266
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,520
Well, you should know,
I can't find him either.

267
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,960
No one can.

268
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,440
That happens now and then.

269
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:21,760
MISSY: Not like this.

270
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,600
It's a confession dial.

271
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,160
A what?

272
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:34,040
MISSY: In your terms, a will.

273
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,880
The last Will and Testament
of the Time Lord known as the Doctor,

274
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,400
to be delivered, according
to ancient tradition,

275
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:44,280
to his closest friend
on the eve of his final day.

276
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,280
-(LOUD ZAP)
-Uh-uh!

277
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:52,920
What are you doing?

278
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,800
You said... I thought...

279
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,640
No, no, no!
It was delivered to me.

280
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,880
-You?
-Of course, it was sent to me.

281
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:01,000
What have you got to do with it?
You're just...

282
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,240
-I'm just what?

283
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,840
You see that couple over there?

284
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,240
You're the puppy.

285
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,520
Since when do you care about the Doctor?

286
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,600
MISSY: Since always.

287
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,240
Since the Cloister Wars.

288
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:18,000
Since the night he stole the moon
and the President's wife.

289
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:20,160
Since he was a little girl.

290
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:23,240
One of those was a lie.
Can you guess which one?

291
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:25,160
He's not your friend.
You keep trying to kill him.

292
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,760
He keeps trying to kill me.

293
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,400
It's sort of our texting.

294
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:30,920
We've been at it for ages.

295
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:32,480
Oh, it must be love.

296
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:33,760
Oh, don't be disgusting.

297
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,400
We're Time Lords, not animals!

298
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:38,800
Try, nano-brain, to rise above
the reproductive frenzy

299
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,960
of your noisy little food chain
and contemplate friendship.

300
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,000
A friendship older
than your civilisation

301
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:49,080
and infinitely more complex.

302
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,920
So the Doctor is your bezzie mate

303
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,200
and I'm supposed to believe
that you've turned good.

304
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,280
Good?

305
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,720
MAN: Man down!

306
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,120
Don't shoot her. Do not shoot her!

307
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:06,800
By the ring on his finger,
he was married,

308
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:10,320
and I think I detected some
baby leakage on his jacket,

309
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,120
so he had a family.

310
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:15,320
No, I've not turned good.

311
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:17,720
Nobody fire!

312
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:20,680
Oh, wow, I'm on a roll.
Thanks for bringing spares.

313
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:24,440
Stop it. Just stop it.
Don't shoot anybody else!

314
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,560
Oi, you, sweaty one, on your knees,

315
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,880
let's have a goodbye
selfie for your kids.

316
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,440
Missy! Nobody else!

317
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:31,880
(SIGHS)

318
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:33,320
Say something nice.

319
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,440
CLARA: No!

320
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,800
I'll kill everyone in this square.

321
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,440
Start with me.

322
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,080
Then what?

323
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,840
Hey? You came here for my help.

324
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,920
Because the Doctor is in danger.

325
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:46,320
-Make me believe you.
-How?

326
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,400
Release the planes.

327
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,280
The planes are keeping me alive.

328
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:50,760
I mean, there's, one,
two, three, four, five,

329
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:53,240
six, seven, eight
naughty little snipers ready to kill me.

330
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:55,080
Yeah. On my command.

331
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,760
Your best friend is in danger,

332
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,760
show me how you care. Make me believe.

333
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,080
(BEEPING)

334
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:11,600
(JET ENGINES ROARING)

335
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:15,200
The planes! The planes
are all moving again.

336
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,600
It was only a basic Time Stop,

337
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,960
parlour trick.

338
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,200
I couldn't have done
anything with them anyway.

339
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,520
What does it say?

340
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,840
MISSY: What does what say?

341
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,040
His confession.

342
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,600
It will only open when he's dead.

343
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:33,680
Then it won't open, will it?

344
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:41,280
Question. If the Doctor
has one last night to live,

345
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:44,080
if he is certain he's facing
the end of his life,

346
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:47,000
where, in all of space and time,
would he go?

347
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,280
Here.

348
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:51,160
(CHEERING)

349
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:54,280
Yes, Earth, obviously, but where? When?

350
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,480
(CHEERING)

351
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:03,320
The algorithm generates
probabilities based on crisis points,

352
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,200
anomalies, anachronisms, key words.

353
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,280
KATE: Such as?

354
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,640
Blue box, Doctor...

355
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,080
BORS: Magician!

356
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,600
There we go. San Martino, Troy,

357
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:17,040
multiples for New York,
and three possible versions of Atlantis.

358
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,760
JAC: It's easier than you'd think.

359
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:22,600
The Doctor makes a lot of noise, and he
loves to make an entrance.

360
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,040
(CHEERING)

361
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:26,640
Which one is the one? Where is he now?

362
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,840
How is a Time Lord supposed to die?

363
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,360
MISSY: Meditation.
Repentance and acceptance.

364
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,880
Contemplation of the absolute.

365
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,120
Great thanks.

366
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:40,800
Change the algorithm.
Eliminate the crisis points.

367
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:44,440
Where is the Doctor making the most
noise, but there isn't any crisis?

368
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,440
(SIGHS) We're looking for a party.

369
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:51,720
(BEEPING)

370
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:57,880
There he is.

371
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,240
(PINGING)

372
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:02,120
"Do not go gentle into that good night."

373
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,920
You go, girl!

374
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,720
(WHOOPING)

375
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,040
Whoo! Mummy, do it again!

376
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:15,560
Vortex manipulators,
yours is slave to mine.

377
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:17,800
Cheap and nasty time travel.

378
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,400
Face me, Magician!

379
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:22,240
Face me!

380
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,640
Oh, you probably want
to throw up, don't you?

381
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,720
Pick a local.

382
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,960
According to you,
this is where the Doctor is.

383
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:30,440
How do we find him?
How do we know what we're looking for?

384
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,640
Anachronisms.

385
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,360
-The slightest, tiniest...
-(ELECTRIC GUITAR SQUEALING)

386
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:39,520
-Anachronisms.
-(ELECTRIC GUITAR PLAYING)

387
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:49,920
(CROWD CHEERING)

388
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:21,000
(CROWD CHEERING)

389
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,560
(GUITAR SQUEALS)

390
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,960
Dude!

391
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:32,080
What is that?

392
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,200
You said you wanted an axe fight.

393
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:36,120
(CHATTER)

394
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,200
Oh, come on,

395
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:39,760
in a few hundred years

396
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:41,200
that will be really funny.

397
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,800
It's a slow burner.

398
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:44,720
BORS: A musical instrument
is not an axe.

399
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:47,840
Yes, and a daffodil is not a broadsword,

400
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,880
but I still won the last round.

401
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,280
(CROWD CHEERING)

402
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:54,880
DOCTOR: What do you think of my tank?
Don't worry, it isn't loaded.

403
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:55,960
I don't like it.

404
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:58,520
No, neither do I.
I bought it for my fish.

405
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,160
BORS: Your fish?

406
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:02,480
I may have ordered online.

407
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,400
Oh, come on!

408
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,400
Fish, tank,

409
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:10,760
honestly, this stuff will be hilarious
in a very few hundred years,

410
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,040
do please stick around.

411
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:14,080
What's the matter with him?
He's never like this.

412
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,800
MISSY: Oh, you really are new,
aren't you?

413
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:20,280
Wait, hang on. Did he just hear that?

414
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,720
He doesn't know we're here, does he?

415
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:25,200
(PLAYING OH, PRETTY WOMAN)

416
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:38,960
Now, you lot.

417
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:43,120
I have been here all day,
and it's been a great day!

418
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:45,000
You've been here for three weeks!

419
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:47,800
Three weeks?

420
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,400
It must be nearly bedtime.

421
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,600
Well, we've partied.

422
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,560
-(CROWD CHEERING)
-Yes!

423
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,560
I helped you dig a well,

424
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:02,760
with a first class,
child-friendly visitor's centre.

425
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:05,520
I've given you some
top notch maths tuition

426
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,440
in a fun, but relevant way.

427
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:10,680
And I've also introduced the word "dude”

428
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,360
several centuries early.

429
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,440
Let me hear you!

430
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,880
ALL: Dude!

431
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,440
Are you a Renaissance...

432
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,520
ALL: Dude!

433
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:18,760
DOCTOR: Are you a Medieval...

434
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:19,840
ALL: Dude!

435
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:21,400
I am a dragon slaying...

436
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,480
ALL: Dude!

437
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:23,840
Where are all the young...

438
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,840
ALL: Dudes!
DOCTOR: I like it.

439
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,640
But I've got some sad news
for you, dudes.

440
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,880
Tonight, I'm going to have to leave you.

441
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,280
CROWD: No!

442
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:33,960
But before I do,

443
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:38,400
I'd like you to meet
a couple of friends of mine.

444
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,920
(CROWD CHEERING)

445
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,920
(APPLAUSE)

446
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,640
How did you know I was here?
Did you see me?

447
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:54,640
When do I not see you?

448
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,560
What, one face in all of that crowd?

449
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,960
There was a crowd, too?

450
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,120
Wow, we're doing charm
as well now, are we?

451
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,480
(CHUCKLING) Which one of us dying?

452
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:09,280
OK.

453
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,440
And we're doing hugging now too.
I can't keep up.

454
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,040
Well, you know what they say.

455
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:16,400
Hugging is a great way
to hide your face.

456
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:21,280
OK, look. I guessed a party,
but not like this.

457
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:22,360
What is this?

458
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:24,920
This isn't you.

459
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,080
I spent all day yesterday in a bow tie.

460
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:30,080
The day before in a long scarf.

461
00:26:30,840 --> 00:26:33,440
It's my party and all of me is invited.

462
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,440
(PLAYING GUITAR)

463
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:42,280
What the hell are you up to, man?

464
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,360
It's the wicked stepmother.

465
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,760
Everyone, hiss.

466
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,600
-(STRUMMING GUITAR)
-(CROWD BOOING)

467
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:52,800
Apparently you think
you're going to die tomorrow.

468
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,720
Well, I've got some good news
about that.

469
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,000
-Oh, yeah?
-It's still today!

470
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,080
Oh, that's very good.

471
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:01,320
(CHOKING)

472
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,400
Bors.

473
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:04,040
Is it a marble again?

474
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:06,560
Did you swallow one
of the marbles I gave you?

475
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,160
Don't swallow marbles!

476
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,240
(CHOKING)

477
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,800
(SNAKE HISSING)

478
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,400
(CROWD GASPING)

479
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:20,120
Doctor.

480
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,880
Your friends have led me to you.

481
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:26,320
You will come.

482
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:28,120
Says you and whose army?

483
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,520
(CROWD SCREAMING)

484
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,080
(SNAKES HISSING)

485
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:46,840
Nobody dies here.

486
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,840
Not one person, not one of my
friends, do you understand?

487
00:27:51,320 --> 00:27:54,240
Davros, creator of the Daleks,

488
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:57,600
Dark Lord of Skaro, is dying.

489
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,280
So I hear.

490
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:03,200
He would speak with you again
on the last night of his life.

491
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:05,080
Then you will harm nobody in this place.

492
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,800
Not one person. Are we very, very clear?

493
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:09,600
(HISSING)

494
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,800
(SNAKES HISSING)

495
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:28,240
Are you so dangerous, little man?

496
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:34,440
You want to know how dangerous I am?

497
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:35,720
Davros sent you.

498
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:37,200
You know how stupid you are?

499
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,560
(SCOFFS) You came!

500
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:40,120
(HISSES)

501
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,640
Is that supposed to frighten me?

502
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,520
Snake nest in a dress!

503
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:47,040
Now, explain politely.

504
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:51,960
Davros is my archenemy.
Why would I want to talk to him?

505
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,520
Hang on a minute.
Davros is your archenemy now?

506
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,520
-Hush!
-I'll scratch his eye out.

507
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:59,200
Davros knows.

508
00:29:00,360 --> 00:29:02,360
Davros remembers.

509
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:16,880
That's yours.

510
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:21,120
Uh, it was.

511
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:24,120
Was?

512
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:27,240
I don't have a screwdriver any more.

513
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,960
Ooh!

514
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,800
Never seen that before.

515
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:35,480
Doctor, the look on your face.

516
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:37,280
What is that?

517
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:39,040
Shame.

518
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,920
You're ashamed.

519
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,280
Doctor?

520
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:52,600
What have you done?

521
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:56,000
YOUNG DAVROS:
Please, you've got to help me.

522
00:29:57,600 --> 00:30:01,120
You said I could survive,
you said you'd help me!

523
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:05,760
Help me!

524
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:21,480
Is your ship in orbit?

525
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,520
It's a trap.

526
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,640
Prepare yourself for teleport.

527
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:28,760
Doctor, listen to me.
I know traps. Traps are my flirting.

528
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,200
This is a trap!

529
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:33,680
I am prepared.

530
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:36,040
You sent me your confession dial.

531
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:39,240
You threw yourself a three-week party.
You know what this is!

532
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:40,400
Yes.

533
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,520
Goodbye.

534
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,200
Goodbye, Clara.

535
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,160
(HISSING)

536
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:05,040
We're coming with him.

537
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,640
Both of us, her and me.

538
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,960
No, no, no, no! Under no circumstances!

539
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,680
-What are you doing now?
-Voting.

540
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:15,440
We are a democracy.

541
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:17,920
It is agreed.

542
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:20,520
No, no, no! I forbid it. No!

543
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,040
No! No!

544
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:23,360
No! No!

545
00:31:58,640 --> 00:31:59,760
(BEEPING)

546
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:02,920
Inform high command. It is located.

547
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:06,080
The Tardis is located.

548
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:08,960
DALEX: The Tardis will be procured.

549
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:11,920
Procure the Tardis. Procure the Tardis.

550
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,680
Procure. Procure.

551
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,520
Davros is the child of war.

552
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,120
A war that wouldn't end,
a thousand years of fighting,

553
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,560
till nobody could remember why.

554
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:26,840
So, Davros, he created
a new kind of warrior,

555
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:29,120
one that wouldn't bother
with that question.

556
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:33,880
A mutant in a tank
that would never, ever stop.

557
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:36,640
And they never did.

558
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:38,520
The Daleks.

559
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,040
How scared must you be,

560
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:46,680
to seal every one of your own kind
inside a tank?

561
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,760
(BEEPING)

562
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:54,440
Davros made the Daleks.

563
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,600
But who made Davros?

564
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:03,160
OK, great. Coming out of hyperspace.

565
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:08,880
So that's where he ended up.

566
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:11,000
CLARA: What is that?

567
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:12,280
DOCTOR: I don't know.

568
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:13,920
A hospital?

569
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,320
(MISSY SINGING)

570
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:29,000
How long have we been waiting?

571
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,480
Who knows?

572
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:32,600
It's always the way with hospitals.

573
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,320
You will come.

574
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:42,600
You will stay.

575
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,080
Fair enough.

576
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:45,760
Doctor.

577
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,720
You sent Missy your confession dial.

578
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:54,200
Well, we've known
each other a long time.

579
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,560
She's one of my own people.

580
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:58,360
My point is, we both saw her
die on Earth, ages ago.

581
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:01,760
And obviously you knew that wasn't real,
or worse, hoped it wasn't.

582
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:06,200
Either way, I think you've been lying.

583
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,320
I'm sorry.

584
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,800
Don't apologise. Make it up to me.

585
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,080
There, see, ha!

586
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:18,400
Now you have to come back.

587
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,040
(HISSING)

588
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,240
Gravity.

589
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,000
I know.

590
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,440
-Gravity?
-Oh, yeah.

591
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:47,560
You know what's wrong
with the gravity in here?

592
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,680
-No.
-Nothing.

593
00:34:51,640 --> 00:34:52,760
It's perfect.

594
00:34:53,120 --> 00:34:56,120
But this is a space station,
so the gravity should be

595
00:34:56,200 --> 00:34:59,560
artificial, all coppery-smelling
round the edges,

596
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,480
a tiny bit sexy.

597
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,480
But, this feels real, man.

598
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:06,680
Like a planet.

599
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:09,080
How can you and the Doctor be friends?

600
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:11,280
-Why shouldn't we be?
-You spend all your time fighting.

601
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:13,080
-Exactly.
-(HISSING)

602
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:16,800
MISSY: You know what this airlock is?

603
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:18,240
I'll tell you.

604
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:20,960
-It's pants.
-What do you mean?

605
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:24,800
I mean that today might be the day.

606
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,280
What day?

607
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:27,880
The day I kill you.

608
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:29,880
What are you doing? Are you opening it?

609
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:30,960
MISSY: Yeah, of course.

610
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:33,200
Missy, we'll get sucked out!

611
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:34,840
You and me together, off we go!

612
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,360
Let's make jam!

613
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,120
(ELECTRONIC PULSE)

614
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,640
(BEEPING)

615
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:00,360
Doctor?

616
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:24,400
Doctor!

617
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,520
Davros.

618
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:31,920
DAVROS: I approve of your new face,
Doctor.

619
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:35,800
So much more like mine.

620
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:40,800
Colony Sarff, untie our guest's hands.

621
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,160
(COLONY SARFF HISSING)

622
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:46,680
DAVROS: You may leave us.

623
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:50,880
You came, then?

624
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:53,520
Clearly.

625
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:56,200
Did you suspect a trap?

626
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:58,880
I still do.

627
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:02,520
Then why are you here?

628
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:06,640
Did you miss our conversations?

629
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:11,960
THE FOURTH DOCTOR: If you had created
a virus in your laboratory...

630
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:13,960
THE FIFTH DOCTOR:
I'm not here as your prisoner, Davros!

631
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:16,960
THE SEVENTH DOCTOR: Unimaginable
power, unlimited rice pudding...

632
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,640
THE TENTH DOCTOR:
Everything we saw, everything we lost...

633
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:21,120
THE SIXTH DOCTOR:
But did you bother to tell anyone

634
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,640
they might be eating
their own relatives?

635
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,520
Yes, yes, OK,
you've made your point.

636
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:25,920
Have I?

637
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:28,640
If someone who knew the future

638
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,560
pointed out a child to you
and told you that that child

639
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:33,320
would grow up totally evil,

640
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:36,680
to be a ruthless dictator
who would destroy millions of lives,

641
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:38,480
could you then kill that child?

642
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:40,520
I get the point.

643
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:43,720
Do you know why you came, Doctor?

644
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:47,320
You have a sense of duty.

645
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:48,600
Of guilt, perhaps.

646
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:52,320
And certainly of shame.

647
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,040
You flatter me.

648
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,760
A pity.

649
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:59,840
I intended to accuse.

650
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:07,600
I believe that
for the ultimate good of the universe

651
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:10,680
I was right to create the Daleks.

652
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:12,880
You were very wrong.

653
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:16,040
DAVROS: This is the argument
we've had since we met.

654
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,640
It ended in the Time War.

655
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:20,080
It survived the Time War,

656
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:24,080
but it will end tonight.

657
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:26,920
That is why you are here.

658
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,400
(ALARM SOUNDING)

659
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:31,840
It seems your friends
have gone exploring.

660
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:38,760
It's warm, isn't it?

661
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:42,320
For deep space, anyway.

662
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:47,760
CLARA: What are you doing?

663
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:49,760
MISSY: Treading softly.

664
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:04,120
Oh, there's a floor?

665
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:05,200
MISSY: No.

666
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,200
No, there's ground.

667
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,680
This is the ground.

668
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,280
We're on a planet!

669
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,760
And that is not a space station,

670
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,720
that is a building,

671
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:26,320
and the rest of the planet,
the whole thing, is invisible.

672
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,760
That's ridiculous.

673
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,160
MISSY: Well, yes, of course it is.

674
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:30,920
I mean, how would you
ever find your glasses,

675
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:32,720
or the little girls' room and...

676
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:34,400
What if you kissed an ugly?

677
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:38,000
Unless, when you're part of
the atmosphere,

678
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,840
you start syncing with the spectrum.

679
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:46,600
Why would anybody hide a whole planet?

680
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,680
That would rather depend
on the planet, dear.

681
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,120
No!

682
00:39:58,080 --> 00:39:59,080
No!

683
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,560
They've built it again.
They've brought it back.

684
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:03,160
No! No! No!

685
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,640
What? What is it? Where are we?

686
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:07,720
Skaro!

687
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:10,560
You brought me to Skaro!

688
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:13,640
Where does an old man go to die,

689
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,360
but with his children?

690
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,200
(PANTING)

691
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:19,520
What's Skaro?

692
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,240
MISSY: The beginning.

693
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:24,520
Where it all started.

694
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:28,000
This is the planet of the Daleks.

695
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,040
DALEK: Correct!

696
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,560
Clara!

697
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:37,440
You cannot help her now, Doctor.

698
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:39,120
(GRUNTS)

699
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:54,240
CLARA: The Tardis.

700
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:56,040
How did she get here?

701
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,840
It has been procured.

702
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:06,520
Yeah? Yeah, well, if you're
trying to get inside, you can't.

703
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,360
Nothing can enter the Tardis.

704
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:12,200
The Tardis will not be entered.

705
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:15,480
The Tardis will be destroyed.

706
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:18,440
(LAUGHS) Well, good luck,
because she's indestructible.

707
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:19,520
Did the Doctor tell you that?

708
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:21,680
'Cause you should never
believe a man about a vehicle.

709
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:23,200
What are they going to do?

710
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,480
Who can say?

711
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:26,680
You know what children are like.

712
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:30,040
MISSY: Daleks, pay attention!

713
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:33,440
Don't. Just don't.

714
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,040
You know what this is?

715
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:37,680
This thing you're about to destroy?

716
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,520
I'll tell you.

717
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:43,200
It's the dog's unmentionables.

718
00:41:43,520 --> 00:41:46,200
And you know all about those, don't you?

719
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,800
This is a Tardis.

720
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:51,720
Now, with this you can
go anywhere, do anything,

721
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:52,920
kill anyone.

722
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:57,480
With this, the Daleks
can be more powerful than ever before.

723
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,880
You just need one thing.

724
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:05,320
No. Missy, no!

725
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:06,680
Me!

726
00:42:07,680 --> 00:42:09,080
You need me!

727
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:12,360
A Time Lady to show you how it works.

728
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,880
With this and with me,

729
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:16,720
everything can be yours,

730
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:21,480
and you can burn it all,
forever and ever and ever.

731
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:31,040
Or would you rather just kill me?

732
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:35,840
Maximum extermination.

733
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,120
Exterminate!

734
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,280
Please!

735
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,560
(PANTING)

736
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:45,320
Please, I'm begging you, please!

737
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,640
Please. Please save Clara.

738
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:49,880
I gave the Daleks life.

739
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,240
I do not control them.

740
00:42:58,680 --> 00:42:59,840
Oh, Clara.

741
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:02,240
Oh, my Clara.

742
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,840
See how they play with her.

743
00:43:04,920 --> 00:43:07,400
See how they toy! They want her to run.

744
00:43:07,480 --> 00:43:09,480
They need her to run.

745
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:12,120
Do you feel their need, Doctor?

746
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:15,040
Their blood is screaming.

747
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:17,760
Kill! Kill! Kill!

748
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:20,160
Hunter and prey,

749
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:24,000
held in the ecstasy of crisis.

750
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:28,440
Is this not life at its purest?

751
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:46,520
Exterminate! Exterminate!

752
00:43:46,880 --> 00:43:47,880
(SCREAMS)

753
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:55,720
(SIGHS)

754
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,000
Why have I ever let you live?

755
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:06,040
Compassion, Doctor.

756
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:10,760
It has always been
your greatest indulgence.

757
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:14,680
Let this be my final victory.

758
00:44:14,760 --> 00:44:18,880
Let me hear you say it, just once.

759
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:24,800
Compassion is wrong.

760
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,120
Destroy the Tardis!

761
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:31,360
DALEKS: Destroy! Destroy!

762
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:38,400
Destroy! Destroy!

763
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:40,840
Destroy! Destroy!

764
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:42,800
Destroy! Destroy!

765
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,000
YOUNG DAVROS: Help me!

766
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:59,440
You can't leave me, you promised.

767
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:01,640
You said I had a chance.

768
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:03,040
(CLICKING)

769
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:06,440
Who are you?

770
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:09,680
I don't get it.

771
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:11,960
How did you get there?

772
00:45:12,440 --> 00:45:13,680
From the future.

773
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:16,440
Are you going to save me?

774
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:19,120
I'm going to save my friend,

775
00:45:19,600 --> 00:45:20,880
the only way I can.

776
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:23,040
Exterminate!

777
00:45:52,760 --> 00:45:56,280
DAVROS: Imagine to hold in your hand

778
00:45:56,360 --> 00:45:58,600
the heartbeat of every Dalek.

779
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:03,760
Genocide, in a moment.

780
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:09,320
So many backs with a single knife.

781
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:11,720
DALEKS: Always Davros!

782
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:15,320
Are you ready to be a god?

